            <li>Lost funds due to wallet security issues</li>
            <li>Smart contract bugs or exploits</li>
            <li>Network outages or blockchain issues</li>
            <li>Lost profits or opportunity costs</li>
            <li>Third-party actions or content</li>
            <li>Any indirect, incidental, or consequential damages</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>9.3 Open Source Disclaimer</h3>
          <p>
            This is an open-source project maintained by volunteers. There is no guarantee
            of support, updates, or continued operation. You use the Platform at your own risk.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section id="termination">
          <h2>10. Termination</h2>

          <h3>10.1 Your Right to Leave</h3>
          <p>
            You may stop using the Platform at any time. Your on-chain assets (NFTs)
            remain in your wallet regardless of Platform status.
          </p>

          <h3>10.2 Our Right to Terminate</h3>
          <p>
            We may suspend or terminate your access for:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>Violation of these Terms</li>
            <li>Illegal activity</li>
            <li>Abuse of other users</li>
            <li>Attempting to harm the Platform</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>10.3 Effect of Termination</h3>
          <p>
            Upon termination:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>Your account access is revoked</li>
            <li>Off-chain data may be deleted</li>
            <li>On-chain assets remain in your wallet</li>
            <li>You may request data export before termination takes effect</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section id="changes">
          <h2>11. Changes to Terms</h2>
          <p>
            We may modify these Terms. When we do:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>We will post the updated Terms on this page</li>
            <li>We will update the "Last Updated" date</li>
            <li>Material changes will be announced via the Platform</li>
            <li>Continued use after changes constitutes acceptance</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section id="governing">
          <h2>12. Governing Law</h2>
          <p>
            These Terms shall be governed by applicable law. As a decentralized,
            open-source project:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>Disputes should first be resolved through community mediation</li>
            <li>Smart contract interactions are governed by blockchain protocol rules</li>
            <li>Contributors are subject to laws in their respective jurisdictions</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section id="contact">
          <h2>13. Contact</h2>
          <p>
            For questions about these Terms:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Email:</strong> legal@worldbridger.one</li>
            <li><strong>Discord:</strong> #support channel</li>
            <li><strong>GitHub:</strong> Open an issue for public discussion</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

      </article>

      <footer class="legal-footer">
        <p>
          These Terms are licensed under
          <a href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0/" target="_blank">CC BY-SA 4.0</a>.
        </p>
        <div class="legal-nav">
          <a href="/privacy">Privacy Policy</a>
          <a href="/community-guidelines">Community Guidelines</a>
          <a href="/license">Open Source License</a>
        </div>
      </footer>
